Basic Installation
==================

1. Windows
2. Linux


1. Installing Nemerle on Windows
--------------------------------

Run setup.exe and follow instructions displayed on the screen.


2. Installing Nemerle on Linux
------------------------------

The simpliest way to compile this package is:

  1. Type './configure' to configure the package for your system.
  2. Type 'make' to bootstrap the compiler, and standard library.
  3. Type 'make install' to install compiler, standard library, and
     documentation.

The configure script takes many switches that may affect compilation
process.  Run configure with --help switch to list all supported
options.

If you experience any problems with configure script or compilation
process, please let us know by submitting a bug at
http://nemerle.org/bugs, or by mailing us at feedback@nemerle.org.

